                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.H Continental Solidarity/92: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hull</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-12-21T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 21, 1938—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>84. Your 47, December 20, noon.</p>
                <p>The text quoted in your telegram under reference would seem to me to be a
                    singularly satisfactory solution. The use of the word “extrana” in the second
                    paragraph will in my opinion unquestionably imply extra-continental. I hope it
                    is not premature to offer my heartiest congratulation on what would appear to be
                    a thoroughly satisfactory ending of a protracted discussion.</p>
                <p>I received yesterday a personal message from the Cuban Ambassador expressing his
                    great disappointment that the Cuban resolution on tolerance was being blocked.
                    It would seem to me that the adoption of this resolution would have a singularly
                    happy effect in many quarters.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
